posts.name: Andrew H.
posts.cooked:
I mean, these look to almost certainly be correlation equations. Except possibly the denominator in the RPM calculation being a sort of radius, I doubt that any of these numbers has any meaning beyond, “This is what excel told us the best fit curve was”.

I would hope this snippet is in its own function with the intended functionality documented, but imo it doesn’t make the code more readable to pull all the constants out of the equations. Best you can do is hard-code the two velocity correlations to be the same order polynomial.

Is this actually better?
